# Brand and theme

Match corporate Simple Light presentation standards (~16:9). Full spec: `@docs/PRD.md` §8.

## Brand assets (`public/brand/`)

Use committed assets — do not invent backgrounds or substitute stock imagery.

| File | Layout / usage |
| --- | --- |
| `bg-default.jpg` | Title, title+body, two-column, title-only, Q&A |
| `bg-section-blue.jpg` | Section header (dark field, light text) |
| `bg-section-light.jpg` | Section opener variant (light field) |
| `bg-thankyou.jpg` | Thank-you / strong brand close |
| `logo-mev.png` | White wordmark — top-right on **dark** slides (`section` blue, `thank-you`) |
| `motif-arc.png` | Dark wordmark + arc — top-right on **light** slides; cover hero; bottom-left accent on light section/Q&A |

### Logo contrast

Use `<BrandLogo variant="dark" />` on light backgrounds and `<BrandLogo variant="light" />` on dark backgrounds. Default is `dark`. Cover uses the hero logo centered — no corner `BrandLogo`.

### Editorial figures (`public/brand/figures/`)

B&W vintage cutouts with selective primary-blue accents — part of the corporate look, not generic stock.

| File | Suggested use |
| --- | --- |
| `figure-filmmaker.png` | Title, intro, “observe / document” themes |
| `figure-vintage-tv.png` | Title hero, strong brand moments |
| `figure-retro-computer.png` | Tech / tooling / Cursor-harness topics |
| `figure-pointing-hand.png` | Callouts, bullets, “look here” emphasis |
| `figure-enter-runners.png` | Momentum, action, best-practices sections |
| `figure-crt-communicator.png` | Q&A, communication, stretch content |

**Usage:** 0–1 figure per content slide. **Do not** use `<SectionFigure>` on title+body or two-column slides.

#### Two-column figures (diagrams, screenshots, editorial art)

On `layout: two-cols` slides:

- **Left:** slide title + body copy.
- **Right:** `<TwoColFigure src="/brand/figures/…" alt="…" />` in the `::right::` slot (starts **below** the title line; styling lives in `styles/layouts.css` — do not hand-roll `img` classes).
- Optional attribution under the figure: `<p class="two-col-figure-source">…</p>`.
- Non-image right column (e.g. a table): wrap in `<div class="two-col-right-slot">…</div>` for the same vertical alignment.

Diagrams and workshop screenshots live under `public/brand/figures/` (e.g. `diagram-*.png`, `sample-agents-md.png`).

#### Cover hero only (`SectionFigure`)

Use `<SectionFigure>` **only** on the **cover** slide (`position="bottom"` or `right` per layout). Section headers may use it sparingly; never mix with `TwoColFigure` on the same slide.

Slides 19–21 in the PowerPoint are asset-catalog demos — do not replicate that collage layout.

## Color tokens

Prefer CSS variables over one-off hardcodes:

| Token | Hex | Usage |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Primary | `#002894` | Section headers, strong brand fields |
| Accent | `#4285F4` | Highlights |
| Soft blue | `#B8CBFF` | Secondary panels |
| Dark | `#212126` / `#000000` | Body text |
| Light | `#FFFFFF` / `#EEEEEE` | Backgrounds |
| Link | `#0097A7` | Hyperlinks |

Amber / cyan / lime accents sparingly only if matching the template.

## Typography

- Display / titles: Oswald (Google Fonts or equivalent geometric sans)
- Body: Arial or equivalent clean sans

## Layout vocabulary

Implement: title, section header, title+body, title+two columns, title-only, Q&A, thank-you. Contact only if the template requires a close layout.

Map each layout to the background asset above; place logo and motif consistently per PRD §8.

## Do not

```text
❌ Keep @slidev/theme-seriph as visual identity
❌ Purple-on-white / generic “AI gradient” aesthetics
❌ Invent a new brand system or ad-hoc backgrounds
❌ Use random stock photos outside the committed figure set
❌ Replicate the PowerPoint asset-catalog collage slides (19–21)
```

```text
✅ Encode tokens in theme/CSS; reference public/brand/ assets
✅ Mirror corporate layouts, not default Slidev starter chrome
```
